  "title": "Furniture Delivery Driver and Installer",
  "description": "<h4>Job Offers &amp; Benefits:</h4>\n<p>· <strong>$2500-$3300 basic salary</strong></p>\n<p>· <strong>Team/Personal Incentive &amp; overtime</strong></p>\n<p>· <strong>Variable performance bonus</strong></p>\n<p>· <strong>Incremental annual leave yearly (12 to 18 days)</strong></p>\n<p>· <strong>Staff credit for free product and discount on product purchase yearly.</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>We are looking for a <strong>team player</strong> to join our growing Singapore Furniture Brand. Your achievement in building customer satisfaction is our success.</p>\n<h4><strong>Candidate Role:</strong></h4>\n<p>Warehouse logistics, furniture assembly, delivery and repair.</p>\n<h4>Job Responsibility:</h4>\n<p>· Warehouse housekeeping and efficient storage for smooth workflow.</p>\n<p>· Stock-In: unloading area (count), holding area (sort) and stowing area (label).</p>\n<p>· In-Stock: Inspect stock and delivery items to label and highlight issues.</p>\n<p>· Stock-Out picking and sorting for work/delivery order and return and pack daily.</p>\n<p>· Delivery and Assembly of furniture (driver</p>\n<p>· Repair and Maintenance of furniture.</p>\n<p>· Ensuring the warehouse are clean and equipment well maintained. Stacker &amp; pallet jack.</p>\n<p>· Comply to safety regulations and security measures for warehouse operations.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>· <strong>货舱运作：分类拣货盘点货物</strong></p>\n<p>· <strong>家具送货，组装和安装和包装家具</strong></p>\n<p>· <strong>修理 家具 和 电动机械功能</strong></p>\n<p>· <strong>协助装载和卸载重型家具，体格强壮</strong></p>\n<p>· <strong>为所有交付工作提供优质的客户服务</strong></p>\n<p>· <strong>确保客户安装位置和送货车辆的清洁度</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p>\n<p>v Class 3 or 4 driving License is required for full/part time driver.</p>\n<p>v Training expense provided, if below experience or certification for forklift or stacker license.</p>\n<p>v Experience in organising inventory and warehouse operations.</p>\n<p>v Experience in furniture house moving and furniture installation.</p>\n<p>v Experience in furniture carpentry &amp; mechanical/electrical servicing.</p>\n<p>v Experience in using inventory software to create SKU &amp; barcoding will be a plus.</p>\n<p>v Ability to operate power and hand tools, hydraulic jack &amp; forklift or stacker.</p>\n<p>v General good health to handle physical activity of carrying heavy items.</p>\n<p>v Self-motivated to learn about our products parts, independent and a fast learner</p>\n<p>v 5-day work week shift (Mon-Fri &amp; Tue-Sat), daily (8 hours work &amp; 1 hour meal) with overtime during peak period.</p>\n<p>v Able to start with short notice period.</p>",
